Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).
Once hot, fry the @British Beef Mince{240%g}, ~{5-6%minutes}. Break up the mince
as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's
> no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pour the boiling water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on
high heat.

Boil the @Basmati Rice{150%g}, ~{10-12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain, pop back in
the pan and cover.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @Mixed Beans{1%carton}.

Add the @Tomato Puree{30%g} to the beef. Cook, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the beans, @Red Wine Stock Paste{28%g}, @Chipotle Paste{20%g} (add less
if you'd prefer things milder), @Honey{1%tbsp} and @Water for the Sauce{100%ml}.
Bring to the boil and simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove from the heat. Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the beef chilli.

Drizzle over the @Soured Cream{75%g}.

Enjoy!